ian's Wall was built across northern England. The name was later taken by several early popes, including the only English pope,  Nicholas Breakspeare  (Adrian IV). It was in early use among immigrants from the Low Countries, and is found in some English regions from the mid-16th century. It has enjoyed considerable popularity in the English-speaking world since the late 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adriaen De Brier was born in 1545, in Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. He died in 1582, in Frankenthal, Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1545–1582":"1545–1582","1553–1659":"1553–1659","–Female":"Surnud","1575–1645":"1575–1645","1645":"1645","1545":"1545","1575":"1575","1553":"1553","1582":"1582","1 December 1575":"1. detsember 1575","1659":"1659","Frankenthal, Frankenthal, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Frankenthal, Landkreis Frankenthal, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Frankenthal, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Frankenthal, Frankenthal, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Frankenthal, Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1545–1582":"1545–1582","1553–1659":"1553–1659","–Female":"Kuollut","1575–1645":"1575–1645","1645":"1645","1545":"1545","1575":"1575","1553":"1553","1582":"1582","1 December 1575":"1. joulukuuta 1575","1659":"1659","Frankenthal, Frankenthal, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Frankenthal, Landkreis Frankenthal, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Frankenthal, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa","Frankenthal, Frankenthal, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Frankenthal, Frankenthal (Pfalz), Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksa"},"fr":{"1545–1582":"1545–1582","1553–1659":"1553–1659","–Female":"Décédée","1575–1645":"1575–1645","1645":"1645","1545":"1545","1575":"1575","1553":"1553","1582":"1582","1 December 1575":"1 décembre 1575","1659":"1659","Frankenthal, Frankenthal, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany":"Frankenthal, 